                <note rend="inline" type="source">211.18/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-18T18:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 19—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Department’s instruction number 91, August 22nd. Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    after a consultation with members of Congress agrees to Department’s suggestion
                    for ratification of Extradition Convention and exchange of notes. Chairman of
                    the Committee on Foreign Affairs maintains that convention as ratified by Costa
                    Rican Congress and approved by the President cannot be resubmitted under the
                    rules of Costa Rican Congress and advises signing a new convention. I have urged
                    resubmission. Minister for Foreign Affairs will leave for vacation very soon and
                    has expressed a desire to submit convention before leaving and while Congress is
                    in extra session; also desires notes exchanged here if possible. Respectfully
                    request cable instructions and information about procedure to be followed in
                    ratification and exchange of notes also full power in case of necessity of
                    signing another convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
